                    <title>Don&#039;t Let Your Methods Look Like This!</title>
                    <link rel="alternate" href="http://coderetreat.org/xn/detail/6456126:BlogPost:6791"/>
                                        <id>tag:coderetreat.org,2012-01-09:6456126:BlogPost:6791</id>
                                        <updated>2012-01-09T16:50:55.000Z</updated>
                    
                                            <author>
                            <name>Alexandru Bolboaca</name>
                            <uri>http://coderetreat.org/profile/AlexandruBolboaca</uri>
                        </author>
                    
                    <summary type="html">
                        &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.alexbolboaca.ro/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/DontLetYourMethodLookLikeMe-e1302082426239.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Don&#039;t Let Your method look like me!&quot; class=&quot;alignleft size-medium wp-image-456&quot; height=&quot;300&quot; src=&quot;http://www.alexbolboaca.ro/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/DontLetYourMethodLookLikeMe-e1302082426239-225x300.jpg&quot; title=&quot;DontLetYourMethodLookLikeMe&quot; width=&quot;225&quot;&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I drew this picture with Corey Haines at the Krakow April 2011 Code Retreat. I started with the overall silhouette of the method, and Corey added the eye and the comment. In the end, I think we got an excellent motivational poster. So, developers, don&#039;t let your methods look like this!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The right bottom corner is about another thing you should…&lt;/p&gt;                    </summary>

                    <content type="html">
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.alexbolboaca.ro/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/DontLetYourMethodLookLikeMe-e1302082426239.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.alexbolboaca.ro/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/DontLetYourMethodLookLikeMe-e1302082426239-225x300.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Don&#039;t Let Your method look like me!&quot; title=&quot;DontLetYourMethodLookLikeMe&quot; class=&quot;alignleft size-medium wp-image-456&quot; width=&quot;225&quot; height=&quot;300&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I drew this picture with Corey Haines at the Krakow April 2011 Code Retreat. I started with the overall silhouette of the method, and Corey added the eye and the comment. In the end, I think we got an excellent motivational poster. So, developers, don&#039;t let your methods look like this!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The right bottom corner is about another thing you should remember: at least know the name of your pair before starting to program. It&#039;s funny how many times I&#039;ve seen developers jumping right into the problem and forget this simple thing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the end, many thanks to the people who made the Code Retreat Krakow such an amazing experience. Pair facilitating with Corey is always an awesome experience, and I&#039;d love to do it more often. I loved the energy of the participants and I&#039;m really proud of the T-Shirt. Corey, Krakow, see you again soon!&lt;/p&gt;</content>
